The is WebAppMapper - a firefox extension that helps to map 
web application functionality during the first phase of
access control flaws discovery.

To now, the only way to install the extension is as follows:
 * Locate your FF profile folder (~/.mozilla/firefox/<profile name> in linux)
 * Create the folder named webappmapper@lvk.cs.msu.su at the "extensions" subfolder
 * Copy the files from src directory to the newly created folder
 * Start firefox

WARNING: It is highly recommended not install this experimental extension into your
working profile. Create another one instead!
